text: If other was selected, please specify:

The items that follow are phrases that describe how children may act. Please read each phrase, and mark the response that describes how this child has behaved recently (in the last several months).  Please mark every item. If you don't know or are unsure of your response to an item, give your best estimate.
Shares toys or possessions with other children.
Speaks in short phrases that are hard to understand.
Eats things that are not food.
Misses school or daycare because of sickness.
Provides own telephone number when asked.
Congratulates others when good things happen to them.
Says, "I'm afraid I will make a mistake."
Decides what clothing to wear without help.
Interrupts others when they are speaking.
Gets very upset when things are lost.
Worries about what other children think.
Adjusts well to new teachers or caregivers.
Worries about things that cannot be changed.
Makes frequent visits to the doctor.
Says all letters of the alphabet when asked.
Encourages others to do their best.
Is chosen last by other children for games.
Fiddles with things while at meals.
Readily starts up conversations with new people.
Fails to wash hands when needed.
Adjusts well to changes in routine.
Shows feelings that do not fit the situation.
Responds appropriately when asked a question.
Says things that make no sense.
Is clear when telling about personal experiences.
Pays attention when being spoken to.
Clings to parent in strange surroundings.
Interrupts parents when they are talking on the phone.
Adjusts well to changes in family plans.
Is able to describe feelings accurately.
Has trouble fastening buttons on clothing.
Says, "I'm not very good at this."
Has trouble eating with a fork.
Disrupts the play of other children.
Needs to be reminded to brush teeth.
